The paper focuses on video understanding and encoding using a novel network module called DenseImage Network (DIN). The paper extensively uses convolutional neural networks (CNN) for video understanding, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a learning strategy based on DenseImage and a temporal-order-preserving CNN network, which involves training the network to capture temporal evolution at multiple time scales with different filter widths. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on two recent challenging benchmarks, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a novel compact representation of video, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
